---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import JournalSubNav from '../../components/JournalSubNav.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Best British Schools in Bangkok — Journal" description="A guide to Bangkok's top-ranked British curriculum schools, covering fees, UK affiliations, and what parents should know.">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <JournalSubNav active="Cities" />

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative w-full h-[60vh] min-h-[400px] overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="/images/bangkok-hero.jpg"
      alt="Bangkok skyline at dusk"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/30 to-transparent"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 p-6 md:p-12">
      <div class="bsa-container max-w-2xl">
        <p class="label text-white/70 mb-4">Cities</p>
        <h1 class="text-white text-3xl md:text-5xl leading-tight">Best British Schools in Bangkok</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ARTICLE BODY -->
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="font-body text-black/50 text-sm mb-8">Published April 2026 &middot; 5 min read</p>

      <div class="space-y-6 font-body text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Bangkok has an unusual concentration of UK-branded schools for a Southeast Asian city. The British Schools Asia index includes four British curriculum schools in Bangkok: Shrewsbury, Wellington College, Brighton College, and Harrow — all operating under licence or affiliation with their UK parent schools. Annual tuition fees range from approximately THB 865,000 to THB 1.2 million (USD 25,200–25,900), placing the four schools in a tight fee band at the upper end of the Bangkok international school market.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/shrewsbury-international-school-bangkok">Shrewsbury International School Bangkok</a> leads the city ranking. Shrewsbury has been operating in Bangkok since 2003 and offers the English National Curriculum through to IGCSE and A Levels. The school has a large campus and a well-established reputation in Bangkok's expat community. Annual fees start from approximately USD 25,900.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/wellington-college-international-school-bangkok">Wellington College International School Bangkok</a>, ranked second in the city, opened more recently and is affiliated with Wellington College in Berkshire. The school follows the English National Curriculum and offers a range of co-curricular activities in line with the Wellington ethos. Fees start from approximately USD 25,200.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Fees in context</h2>

        <p>
          Bangkok's British schools cluster tightly in the fee range of USD 25,200–25,900 per year. This is substantially lower than Singapore (USD 22,500–33,000 at the top schools) or Hong Kong (USD 18,400–26,700 plus debentures), and far below the Chinese cities where fees can exceed USD 40,000.
        </p>

        <p>
          The lower cost of living in Bangkok amplifies this difference. Housing, transport, and daily expenses are a fraction of what families face in Singapore or Hong Kong. For families comparing the total cost of a British education across Asia, Bangkok offers strong value — access to UK-branded schools at Southeast Asian prices.
        </p>

        <p>
          Parents should note that fee structures in Bangkok typically include tuition only. Additional charges for registration, examination fees, school trips, and uniforms are standard. Some schools also charge capital or development levies.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">What parents should know</h2>

        <p>
          The most important consideration in Bangkok is the UK school brand and what it means in practice. All four schools carry the name of a well-known UK school, but the degree of operational connection with the parent school varies. Some schools maintain close links with their UK counterpart in terms of curriculum oversight, teacher exchange, and quality assurance. Others operate more independently under a licensing arrangement.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/brighton-college-bangkok">Brighton College Bangkok</a>, ranked third, is part of the Brighton College International group. <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/harrow-international-school-bangkok">Harrow International School Bangkok</a>, ranked fourth in the city, is one of the longest-established British schools in Bangkok and offers full boarding from Year 7 — a rarity in the Bangkok market.
        </p>

        <p>
          Post-16 pathways vary. Shrewsbury and Harrow offer A Levels, which provides continuity for families committed to the British qualification track. Parents specifically seeking IB Diploma should confirm current offerings directly with each school.
        </p>

        <p>
          Bangkok traffic is a practical factor. School location relative to residential areas matters more than in compact cities like Singapore or Hong Kong. Parents should consider the daily commute before committing to a school.
        </p>

        <p>
          For a full breakdown of every school, visit the <a href="/cities/bangkok">Bangkok city page</a> or browse the <a href="/rankings">full rankings</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <hr class="divider container-narrow" />

  <!-- RELATED -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="label mb-6">Related</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
        <a href="/rankings" class="font-display text-xl no-underline hover:underline" style="text-decoration:none;">
          Asia's Top British Schools — Full Rankings
        </a>
        <a href="/cities/bangkok" class="font-display text-xl no-underline hover:underline" style="text-decoration:none;">
          Bangkok City Guide
        </a>
        <a href="/methodology" class="font-display text-xl no-underline hover:underline" style="text-decoration:none;">
          How We Rank Schools
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
